TITLE: Restaurant CEOs’ new favorite word is value as they aim to bring back customers
SUMMARY: Restaurant CEOs can't stop using the word "value" in explaining lackluster quarterly sales to investors while detailing plans to appeal to thrifty customers.

TITLE: E.l.f. Beauty sales jump 50% on gains in color cosmetics and skin care, launch of Bronzing Drops serum
SUMMARY: E.l.f. Beauty has won over younger consumers with its viral marketing and low-priced "dupes" of prestige favorites.

TITLE: Paramount Global announces it will cut 15% of U.S. workforce, shares rise on second-quarter earnings
SUMMARY: Paramount Global plans to cut 15% of its U.S. workforce as part of a broader $500 million cost reduction.

TITLE: Eli Lilly's blowout quarter should quiet investor concerns about the stock
SUMMARY: Shares of the drugmaker jumped about 8% in Thursday trading after easily beating earnings expectations.

TITLE: Under Armour shares surge 20% after posting 'better than feared' quarterly sales
SUMMARY: Under Armour is in the midst of a broad restructuring as the company contends with a sales slowdown and a revolving door of leaders.

TITLE: Eli Lilly blows past estimates, hikes guidance as Zepbound, Mounjaro sales soar
SUMMARY: The success of Eli Lilly's weight loss and diabetes drugs Zepbound and Mounjaro caused the company to hike its guidance.

TITLE: Restaurant Brands revenue tops estimates, fueled by Tim Hortons
SUMMARY: Canadian coffee chain Tim Hortons was the restaurant company's strongest performer during the quarter.

TITLE: Siemens earnings beat estimates on strong demand for electrification, software
SUMMARY: German industrial technology giant Siemens on Thursday posted better-than-expected quarterly operating profit and confirmed its full-year outlook.

TITLE: Warner Bros. Discovery stock falls as it writes down $9.1 billion, misses estimates
SUMMARY: Warner Bros. Discovery reports earnings after the bell.

TITLE: Disney falls on concerns about its theme park business. Here's why we'd buy the stock
SUMMARY: The entertainment giant delivered the streaming profits we've waited a long time to see.

TITLE: Here's why Eli Lilly is down heading into earnings — and how we plan to play it
SUMMARY: The Investing Club holds its "Morning Meeting" every weekday at 10:20 a.m. ET.

TITLE: Sunrun sees market opportunity after SunPower files for bankruptcy, company's shares surge
SUMMARY: Sunrun posted a surprise profit and sees opportunity to gain market share.

TITLE: CVS slashes profit guidance, will cut $2 billion in expenses as insurance costs climb
SUMMARY: CVS said higher medical costs are weighing on its insurance business, and announced Aetna President Brian Kane will step down.

TITLE: Sony rules out renewing offer for Paramount, says it wouldn't fit strategy
SUMMARY: Hiroki Totoki, Sony's chief financial officer, said the tech giant has no plans to submit a revised offer for Paramount.

TITLE: SoftBank swings back to gains at Vision Fund tech arm, announces up to $3.4 billion share buyback
SUMMARY: SoftBank announced it would buy back up to 6.8% of shares available amounting to up to 500 billion yen ($3.4 billion).

TITLE: Beyonce, PlayStation games help Sony post a 10% jump in profits
SUMMARY: Sony reported a 10% jump in operating profit in the fiscal first quarter, beating analyst expectations.

TITLE: Novo Nordisk shares dip as Wegovy maker posts earnings miss, cuts operating profit outlook
SUMMARY: Novo Nordisk on Wednesday announced its second quarter earnings for 2024.

TITLE: Disney beats estimates as combined streaming services turn a profit
SUMMARY: Disney beat estimates as its combined streaming businesses — Disney+, Hulu and ESPN+ — turned a profit for the first time.

TITLE: Consumer giants from Starbucks to General Mills have one big sales problem: China
SUMMARY: A theme emerging in the latest slew of U.S. companies' earnings reports is a drag from the China market.

TITLE: Rivian tops Wall Street's second-quarter expectations amid cost cuts
SUMMARY: Rivian beat Wall Street's top- and bottom-line expectations for the second quarter as the electric vehicle maker continues to take costs out of its business.

TITLE: Airbnb shares drop 14% on earnings miss as company warns of slowing U.S. demand
SUMMARY: Airbnb shares dropped 14% in after-hours trading after the company reported second-quarter earnings that missed analyst expectations.

TITLE: Yum Brands reports mixed results as Pizza Hut and KFC same-store sales fall
SUMMARY: The restaurant company owns Taco Bell, KFC and Pizza Hut.

TITLE: Uber reports better-than-expected earnings and revenue for second quarter
SUMMARY: Uber reported earnings and revenue that topped estimates for its second quarter.

TITLE: Oil giant Saudi Aramco's second-quarter profit dips 3% on lower crude production volumes
SUMMARY: Saudi Aramco reported $29.1 billion in net profit for the second quarter, a dip of 3% from the same period last year as production volumes remained low.

TITLE: Linde extends its streak of earnings beats, flexes ability to handle any economy
SUMMARY: The industrial gas supplier continues to deliver earnings growth in an "industrial recession" over the past several quarters.

TITLE: Coterra's strong energy production allowed for big cash returns to shareholders
SUMMARY: We're cutting our price target in acknowledgment that commodity prices have come down as the economy is slowing.

TITLE: Berkshire's mounting cash pile could top $200 billion as Buffett continues selling stock
SUMMARY: The Omaha-based conglomerate's cash hoard is likely to exceed its previous record of $189 billion when it reports quarterly earnings Saturday.

TITLE: DraftKings to tax winning bets in high-rate states in a bid to boost profit
SUMMARY: DraftKings will implement a gaming tax on winning bets in some states where the tax rate is highest, including Illinois, New York, Pennsylvania and Vermont.

TITLE: Exxon earnings beat as production in Guyana and Permian sets a record
SUMMARY: Exxon Mobil on Friday posted its second-highest results for the second quarter in the past decade, helped by record production in Guyana and the Permian Basin.

TITLE: Chevron earnings miss on lower refining margins, relocates headquarters to Houston
SUMMARY: The results come as the Chevron-Hess deal is delayed until well into 2025 due to an arbitration case with ExxonMobil.
